          "id": "tldr-ai:2023-02-23:o005",
          "order": 1,
          "title": "3D OBJECT RECONSTRUCTION FROM A SINGLE IMAGE",
          "summary": "This work uses off the shelf diffusion models to generate a prompt and “dream up” other 2D views for an object given a single image. They then fit a neural radiance field to generate a 3D representation of the object. This hierarchical chaining of models results in extremely compelling results. They also introduce some novel regularization for the final reconstruction step.",
          "url": "https://arxiv.org/abs/2302.10663?utm_source=tldrai",
          "reading_time_minutes": 38,
          "source_domain": "arxiv.org",
          "content_type": "editorial",
          "is_sponsor": false
        },
        {
          "id": "tldr-ai:2023-02-23:o006",
          "order": 2,
          "title": "ANIMATED AI",
          "summary": "A cool collection of novel animations to help understand deep learning concepts like padding, stride, and normalization strategies! They are also permissively licensed if you want to use them for your teaching and presentations.",
          "url": "https://animatedai.github.io/?utm_source=tldrai",
          "reading_time_minutes": 2,
          "source_domain": "animatedai.github.io",
          "content_type": "editorial",
          "is_sponsor": false
        },
        {
          "id": "tldr-ai:2023-02-23:o007",
          "order": 3,
          "title": "LANGUAGE MODELS WITH LIMITED GPU MEMORY",
          "summary": "The high computational and memory requirements of large language model (LLM) inference traditionally make it feasible only with multiple high-end accelerators. FlexGen aims to lower the resource requirements of LLM inference down to a single commodity GPU (e.g., T4, 3090) and allow flexible deployment for various hardware setups. The key technique behind FlexGen is to trade off between latency and throughput by developing techniques to increase the effective batch size.",
          "url": "https://github.com/FMInference/FlexGen?utm_source=tldrai",
          "reading_time_minutes": 8,
          "source_domain": "github.com",
          "content_type": "editorial",
          "is_sponsor": false
        }
      ]
